Standard and Poor's Corp said itdowngraded Baker International Corp and upgraded Hughes Tool Coto reflect the companies' merger into Baker Hughes Inc.    The action affected About 840 mln dlrs of debt securities.    S and P said that depressed market conditions wouldcontinue to constrain the new company's operating earnings andcash flow for several years, despite dominant positions in theoil services industry.    Nonetheless, pro forma debt leverage of about 40 pct shoulddecline within a year to about 35 pct because of proceeds fromasset sales, S and P said.    Cut were Baker International's senior debt to A-minus fromA and commercial paper to A-2 from A-1. The unit BakerInternational Finance NV's senior debt, guaranteed by Baker,was reduced to A-minus from A.    S and P raised Hughes Tool's senior debt to A-minus fromB-plus, subordinated debt BBB-plus from B-minus and commercialpaper to A-2 from C. Reuter&#3;